names.fullName: A proteomic analysis of 14-3-3 binding proteins from developing barley grains.

attributeList.attribute: Alexander RD., Morris PC.
p.c.morris@hw.ed.ac

Originally 52 protein GI accession numbers were provided in Table 1. These were extracted from the text and mapped to Uniprot accession numbers using a perl script. Three GI numbers were incorrect, identifiers ACC synthase GI:112713 identifies a protein from winter squash not barley as stated in Table 1. This is the case for GI:339055 Photosystem 1 reaction centre subunit psaK identifies a human protein and alpha amylase inhibitor GI:578524 which identifies a protein from Tetrahymena capricornis, Chlorophyll ab binding protein GI:3153150 which identifies the protein in Acetabularia mediterranea. One protein were not represented in Uniprot GI:23476275 Soluble starch synthase II. 13 proteins were identified as homologues in rice, arabidopsis and spinach. After correspondence with the authors 1 more protein was added, but four proteins identities remained unresolved.
Extracts were obtained from developing barley grains 14 to 21 days post anthesis and isolated starch granules.
Table 1

To improve resolution of separated isolated proteins; crude grain extracts were fractionated using anion exchange chromatography prior to 14-3-3 pull-down chromatography and the 14-3-3 bound and eluted proteins from grain and starch extracts were separated by 2-DE.
